# .rules ÔÇö a natural-language data query engine (OSS)

> **Single source of truth for this repo ÔÇö read this first.** Humans and AI assistants (Claude, Gemini,
> Codex, ÔÇŽ) follow it; `AGENTS.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, and `GEMINI.md` all point here. Keep it **concise and
> current**: the *plan* lives in [`ROADMAP.md`](./ROADMAP.md), the *why* in
> [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md), the *how-to* in [`CONTRIBUTING.md`](./CONTRIBUTING.md). Don't duplicate them here.

## What this repo is
An **open-source, Apache-2.0**, **modular query engine** written in **Rust**: ask a question in **natural
language** and get an answer **grounded in real data**, by plugging in **any LLM** (Claude, OpenAI, a local
or custom model) and **any data provider** (Polygon for markets, a custom source; prediction markets like
Kalshi later) behind two small traits. **Open-core:** the engine, the adapter SDK, and reference adapters
are OSS; hosted / multi-source / team features are additive commercial layers, never bolted into the core.
**Working name: TBD** (the repo is still named `agent`; the rename is an early task).

> **The one-liner:** *glue any model to any data source and query it in plain English* ÔÇö you bring the
> APIs, the engine makes them speak the same language.

## The shape
A natural-language question Ôćĺ the **`Model`** adapter (an LLM) turns it into a structured query Ôćĺ the
**`DataProvider`** adapter fetches and returns data in the engine's **canonical schema** Ôćĺ the `Model`
composes an answer grounded in that data. Every surface (CLI now, an API later) is a **pure view** of the
engine; nothing downstream ever sees a provider's raw API shape.

> **Status:** early. The engine's two seams (`Model` + `DataProvider`) and the **mock** adapters land
> first, so everything builds, tests, and demos **with no API keys**; the real Claude + Polygon adapters
> come next.

## Commands
| Task | Command |
|------|---------|
| Build | `cargo build` |
| Ask a question | `cargo run -p agent -- ask "ÔÇŽ"` |
| Run with **no API keys** (mock model + mock provider) | append `--mock` |
| Machine output | `cargo run -p agent -- ask "ÔÇŽ" --json` |
| Full local gate before pushing | `cargo xtask ci` (fmt + clippy + build + test + feature powerset + deny) |
| Test (offline, uses recorded fixtures) | `cargo test` |

- **Stable Rust, one workspace.** Live model/provider calls hit HTTP APIs, but the **mock** adapters mean
  every command works offline with no keys and no network.

## Stack & layout
- **Rust** (stable). **LLMs:** provider HTTP APIs (**Claude first**). **Data:** provider HTTP APIs
  (**Polygon first**). Adapters are `reqwest`-based and feature-gated.
```
crates/core       the engine: canonical schema, the Model + DataProvider traits, the NLÔćĺqueryÔćĺanswer flow
crates/models     LLM adapters: claude, (openai/local later), mock
crates/providers  data adapters: polygon, (kalshi/custom later), mock
crates/cli        terminal frontend (lib): `ask` (+ `--json`)
crates/app        the single binary: subcommand dispatch, wires model + provider Ôćĺ core Ôćĺ surface
xtask             build/dev orchestration (dev-only, never shipped)
```

## Invariants ÔÇö do not trade these away
The *why* is in [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md) (Design decisions).
- **Headless engine; every surface is a pure view.** The CLI (and any future API) only render the engine's
  output ÔÇö they never call an LLM or a data provider directly.
- **Two trait seams ÔÇö `Model` and `DataProvider`.** A new LLM or a new data source is a **new adapter and
  nothing else**. The core depends on neither a specific model nor a specific provider.
- **A canonical, versioned schema defeats API drift.** Providers map their raw API Ôćĺ the engine's canonical
  types; the engine and the LLM only ever see canonical data. A provider's breaking change is contained to
  *its* adapter ÔÇö never leaks into the core or a surface.
- **Adapters declare capabilities.** Each adapter states what it can serve (which data kinds, which
  operations), so the engine only plans queries a provider can actually answer.
- **Drift is caught in CI, not in prod.** Every adapter has **golden/contract tests over recorded
  fixtures** (deterministic, offline); a provider or LLM contract change fails CI.
- **Grounded, not advice.** The engine answers from returned data and cites what it used; it is a
  **research/analysis** tool, **not financial advice**. No fabricated numbers.
- **Keyless by default.** The permanent **mock** model + mock provider make the whole thing build, test,
  and demo with no API keys ÔÇö a permanent, first-class pair of adapters.
- **The CLI/API is a contract.** `ask --json` has stable field names + exit codes ÔÇö additive changes only,
  golden-tested.

## Code conventions
- `cargo fmt` + `cargo clippy` clean. **No `unwrap`/`expect`/`panic!` outside tests** (workspace `deny`
  lints; `clippy.toml` re-allows them in tests). Stable Rust, `std`.
- **Error model:** `thiserror` in the library crates (`core`/`models`/`providers`), `anyhow` only at the
  `app` boundary. Errors are values; a failed model/provider call degrades to a clear error, never a panic.
- **`unsafe`:** `#![forbid(unsafe_code)]` across the workspace (no FFI here ÔÇö everything is HTTP + serde).
- **Type the domain:** newtypes and typed canonical schema for entities (instruments, quotes, bars, events,
  ÔÇŽ) ÔÇö never bare strings/floats across the trait boundary. `#[non_exhaustive]` on public types so the
  schema and the wire contract evolve additively.
- **Secrets:** API keys come from **env/config only** ÔÇö never committed, never logged, never in fixtures.
- **Feature flags:** each real adapter (claude, polygon, ÔÇŽ) lives behind a cargo feature; CI builds the
  default set, `--no-default-features`, and the feature powerset.
- **MSRV is pinned** (`rust-version`) and CI-guarded.

## Repo etiquette
- Commits: one logical change each, imperative subject. **Never add AI co-author / attribution trailers.**
  **Never commit secrets or fetched/generated data** (recorded fixtures are curated + license-checked).
- Work in phases (Phase 0 Ôćĺ ÔÇŽ) that ladder to `v0.1.0`. Close each with a tag + a working demo + green CI.
  Record significant, hard-to-reverse decisions in [`ARCHITECTURE.md`](./ARCHITECTURE.md).

